Description:
LEAD DÉVELOPPEUR.SE
See English job posting below.
Chez Thinkwell Studio Montréal, créer des expériences inoubliables pour nos clients est notre raison d'être. Nous nous mettons au défi de concevoir et de produire des expériences collectives spectaculaires et novatrices à l'aide de notre gamme de technologies exclusives de pointe, tout en formant d'excellentes équipes. Thinkwell s'efforce de créer un avenir d'interactions partagées qui soient personnalisées, participatives et génératives.
Afin de proposer des produits et des technologies révolutionnaires, nous recherchons un.e lead développeur.se prêt.e à jouer un rôle essentiel dans la conception de projets qui deviendront la carte de visite de l'entreprise.
Rejoignez-nous pour créer des expériences monumentales !
L’opportunité
Studio Thinkwell Montréal est à la recherche d’une personne aspirant à agir comme mentor, à collaborer et à contribuer à l’intégration de solutions interactives en utilisant une variété de technologies, de la plateforme de développement interne et des résultats des travaux menés en R&D. Le ou la Lead développeur.se interactif a pour mission principale de contribuer à toutes les étapes des projets de développement et d'apporter sa passion et son expertise sur nos projets multimédias multidisciplinaires.
*
Ce que tu feras comprend: *
Superviser et mentorer l'équipe de développement d’un projet;
Définir les activités de développement en conformité avec les spécifications techniques définies par l’architecte;
Collaborer étroitement avec l'architecte logiciel et le responsable de produit afin de définir les objectifs futurs et contribuer aux activités de conception logiciel;
Participer aux activités de planification du projet;
S’assurer que le code produit par l’équipe de développement respecte les spécifications techniques (revues de code, tests unitaires, etc.);
Assister l’équipe de développement dans leurs tâches quotidiennes;
Effectuer la programmation des modules en respectant les normes établies et s’assurer que le développement effectué s’intègre bien au système existant;
Concevoir et appliquer des solutions aux défaillances informatiques tout en perfectionnant les programmes;
Utiliser les bonnes techniques de programmation pour assurer un environnement stable, la qualité, l'efficacité et la pertinence de tout le code.
Atouts souhaités:
Diplôme de premier cycle universitaire en informatique ou domaine connexe;
Formation en médias interactifs (un atout) ;
Une expérience professionnelle considérable en développement logiciel.
Ce que tu dois apporter au rôle comprend:
Expérience de leadership en développement logiciels;
Connaissance en langage de programmation C#, Python et gestionnaire de version (GIT, SVN);
Connaissance d’engin 3D (Unity, Unreal);
Utilisation de logiciels VFX (Max, Touch Designer, des atouts);
Connaissance en Shaders un atout;
Faire preuve de rigueur, méthode, logique et rapidité;
Connaissances en mathématiques 2D et 3D;
Connaissance en expérience usager;
Forte capacité de travailler de manière autonome tout en ayant un fort esprit d’équipe;
Bonnes aptitudes en communication;
Bilinguisme français et anglais.
La rémunération
est établie selon la grille salariale interne en vigueur et le niveau d’expérience du candidat. Notre grille salariale respecte des principes d’équité internes et externes. Poste à temps plein, 40 heures semaine; dans le fuseau horaire de l’heure normale de l’Est.
*
Ce que tu y gagnes* :
Assurances médicale et dentaire;
Une culture d’entreprise qui encourage la conciliation travail-vie personnelle;
Une équipe qui travaille fort et s’amuse tout autant;
Horaire de travail à distance et flexible;
Bureaux situés dans un quartier effervescent à une distance de marche du métro De Castelnau sur la ligne bleue.
À PROPOS DE THINKWELL STUDIO MONTREAL
Thinkwell Studio Montréal est reconnu comme pionnier dans la création d'environnements immersifs et interactifs mêlant harmonieusement art et technologie. L'expérience du client est au cœur de tous les projets que nous entreprenons. Du premier point de contact avec l’usager, qu'il s'agisse d'une application, d'un site Web ou d'une expérience numérique, aux activités et à l'environnement, nous tenons compte de ce que chaque personne voit, entend et ressent, en veillant à ce que son expérience soit mémorable, résonnante et authentique.
Nous sommes fiers de notre travail avec des collaborateurs de tous acabits, qu'il s'agisse de leaders mondiaux comme Google et Warner Bros, de héros locaux comme le Parc Oméga et le pont Jacques Cartier, ou des veilleurs du patrimoine comme la Commission des parcs du Niagara. Notre vivier de talents puise dans l'effervescence et la diversité de Montréal et nous relie à un réseau d'innovateurs de classe mondiale.
*****
*
Lead Developer*
At Thinkwell Studio Montreal, we’re all about creating unforgettable guest experiences. We challenge ourselves to design and produce spectacular and innovative collective experiences using our product line of leading edge proprietary technology, building stellar teams while we’re at it. Thinkwell thrives to create a future of shared interactions that are personalized, participatory and generative.
In order to deliver game-changing products and technology, we’re seeking a Lead Developer willing to play an integral role in shaping projects that will become the calling card of the company.
Join us in crafting monumental experiences!
The opportunity
Thinkwell Studio Montreal is looking for someone who aspires to mentor, collaborate and contribute to the integration of interactive solutions using a variety of technologies, the internal development platform and the results of the work carried out in R&D. The main mission of this Lead developer is to contribute to all stages of development projects and to bring their passion and expertise to our multidisciplinary multimedia projects.
*
What you'll do will include: *
Supervise and mentor the development team of a project.
Define development activities in accordance with the technical specifications defined by the architect.
Work closely with the Software Architect and Product Owner to define future goals and contribute to software design activities.
Participate in project planning activities.
Ensure that the code produced by the team of developers meets the technical specifications (code reviews, unit tests, etc.).
Assist the team of developers in their daily tasks
Program the modules in accordance with established standards and ensure that the development carried out integrates well with the existing system.
Design and apply solutions to computer failures while perfecting applications.
Use good programming techniques to ensure a stable environment, quality, efficiency and relevance of all code.
What it would be nice for you to have:
Undergraduate degree in computer science ore related field;
Training in interactive media (an asset);
Significant professional software development experience.
What we need you to bring to the role:
Leadership experience in software development;
Knowledge of C#, Python programming language and version manager (GIT, SVN);
Knowledge of 3D engines (Unity, Unreal);
Use of VFX software (Max, Touch Designer)(an asset);
Knowledge of Shaders (an asset);
Demonstrate rigor, method, logic and speed;
Knowledge of 2D and 3D mathematics;
Knowledge of user experience;
Strong ability to work independently while having a strong team spirit;
Good communication skills;
Able to communicate in French and English.
What's in it for you:
Health benefits and dental insurance;
A company culture that encourages work-life balance;
A team that loves to work as hard as it likes to play;
Remote and flexible working hours;
Offices in a vibrant neighbourhood a stone's throw from De Castelnau metro station on the Blue line.
The salary
is established according to our internal grid and the candidate’s level of experience. Our salary grid is designed to adhere to internal and external equity principles. This is a full-time position at 40 hours per week, working in the EST time zone.
ABOUT THINKWELL STUDIO MONTREAL
We are the guest experience experts. Designing and producing innovative collective experiences using our product line of leading edge proprietary technology, Thinkwell thrives to create a future of shared experiences that are personalized, participatory and generative.
Thinkwell Studio Montreal is heralded as a pioneer in the creation of immersive and interactive environments seamlessly blending art and technology. Guest experience is at the heart of every project we take on. From the first guest touchpoint, be it an app, website or digital experience, to the entry statement, activities, and the environment, we consider what the guest is seeing, hearing, and feeling, ensuring their experience is memorable, resonant, and authentic to the brand.
We take pride in our work with cherished collaborators of all scales, from global leaders like Google and Warner Bros, to local heroes like Parc Omega and the Jacques Cartier Bridge and all the way to heritage keepers such as Niagara Parks Commission. Our pool of talent draws from the effervescence and diversity of Montreal, connecting us to a network of world class innovators.
Type d'emploi : Temps Plein

Today present on five continents, the LCI Education network has 23 higher education campuses and some 3,000 employees who train more than 17,000 students around the world every year. From one country to another, LCI Education favours the harmonization of its programs which allows for greater flexibility, better control over the quality of its services and a deeper respect for the various cultures it serves.
The company's rapid and sustained growth creates opportunities! You have the opportunity to join a growing global organization that is a leader in its sector. You will join a dynamic, human and united team, within a company whose main objective is to allow people to develop and reach their full potential. You will have the chance to shine, to develop yourself, to broaden your horizons.
As a .Net Developer, you will ensure the proper functioning of computer systems and participate in their evolution. You will collaborate in the planning, analysis, design, development and testing of solutions related to our CRM tool. You will ensure that the chosen solution is the right one for our clients. You will also ensure that other software applications integrate well with the solution.
You will also take charge of escalating and resolving the most complex problems and act as a mentor for the more junior resources in the team.
RESPONSIBILITIES
Design, document and implement new components or enhancements to existing applications and integrations;
Work in collaboration with analysts and architects to define and deliver quality technical solutions that meet requirements;
Design, document and implement unit tests;
Mentor and share knowledge with the team;
Find solutions to problems related to computer systems in production;
Work in an autonomous, dynamic and Scrum / PMP oriented process environment;
REQUIRED QUALIFICATIONS
Training
Experience with various technologies, mainly .Net, MS SQL, SSIS as well as NodeJS, Javascript, HTML 5, etc.
You are a curious person and are willing to question established ideas and learn quickly with the right online training material;
Ability to collaborate, communicate, learn and transfer your knowledge;
Problem solving skills;
Minimum 7 years experience in .net programming.
Minimum 2 years experience in CRM development (MS Dynamics, Salesforce, etc.)
College diploma or Bachelor of Science degree, computer science option or related field;
Good knowledge of MS SQL, SSRS and SSIS an asset;
Bilingualism, oral and written (French and English).
BENEFITS
Unlimited online technical training using leading technology platforms;
Reimbursement of certification exams (under certain conditions);
International organization established for over 50 years;
Constantly growing network;
Workplace daycare;
Regular (permanent) full-time position;
Group insurance;
Retirement savings plan;
Organization located in downtown Montreal; the .Net Developer is therefore based in Montreal, at 1400 du Fort Street.
You want to contribute to innovative projects in collaboration with teams from all sectors? Do you dream of working for a Quebec-based company with an international scope? Do you want to join a diversified and humane team that looks to the future? What are you waiting for?
Please note that only selected candidates will be contacted. To lighten the text, we follow the rule that allows the masculine gender to be used with the value of neutral. We subscribe to an equal access program.

